{
  "stem": "3874.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Just prior to the Anschluss, for instance, there were-- there were Austrian patriots who had painted all over the sidewalks the saying, [NON-ENGLISH], which means, 'Red, white, red, until we die'-- which is the Austrian flag-- red, white, red.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Right after the Anschluss, the Germans started picking up Jewish women, and had them-- gave them pails and brushes, and had them on their knees, scrub the-- scrub the sidewalks to get rid of those slogans.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I saw a lot of that going on, and it started being very spooky.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Almost immediately, the Jewish children, for instance-- amongst other things, they had religion was one the classes that they had in public school.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Well, the Jewish kids had their own religion classes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That was abandoned immediately.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And in addition to that, the Jewish kids, no matter how good a student they were, all the Jewish kids now had to sit at the back of the class.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Suddenly, the kids I used to play soccer with, they didn't want to play with the Jewish kids anymore.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It just was a complete change.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You go into the-- within weeks, within a coupe of weeks or a couple months, you saw signs appearing in the-- in the parks, on the park benches, 'Juden verboten'-- no Jews allowed.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In stores, no entry to Jews.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And you know, no matter where you went, you saw sings of that nature.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I remember I finished the fourth grade in September of '38-- and after that the fifth grade, you start what they call like a high school.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I'd taken the test, I had gotten very excellent grades, but neither my cousin-- who was the same as I was-- or myself were accepted.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They just wouldn't let Jews into the gymnasium, into these high schools.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
